<F P=100> Biotechnology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Introduces Permit System for Biotech Related Equipment Exports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  93FE0804A Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 15 Jun 93 p 
5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 93FE0804A </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] The government will introduce a permit system 
beginning 16 July for the export of biotech-related equipment 
and pathogenic organisms, which can be converted to the 
manufacture of biological weapons. 
  The goal is to prevent the proliferation of weapons to 
volatile regions of the world. Under this system, seven types of 
equipment such as freeze dryers and ultracentrifuges, and 63 
types of pathogens and toxins such as the Japan encephalitis 
virus will be restricted. The system will require exporters to 
report to the Ministry of International Trade and Industry the 
destination, user, intended use, etc., and export will be denied 
if there is a chance that these items might be used to make 
biological weapons. The Diet will revise the Export Trade 
Control Ordinance on 15 June. 
  It was decided to place restrictions on biotech-related 
equipment and pathogenic organisms at the meeting of the 
Australia Group (currently comprised of 25 nations including 
Japan, the U.S. and Europe) held in December 1992 in Paris. 

</TEXT>

