<H3> <TI>   MITI Minister, Israel Trade Minister Agree on Joint Biotech Research Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  93FE0804B Tokyo NIHON KOGYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 16 Jun 93 p 2 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 93FE0804B </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KOGYO SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] On 15 June Israeli Trade Minister Harisshu [phonetic] 
met with MITI Minister Mori at MITI headquarters in Kasumigaseki, 
Tokyo. At this meeting they signed an agreement that the 
Government Industrial Research Institute, Osaka, AIST and Hebrew 
University will begin joint research next year on the high)level 
utilization of microalgae. Mr. Mori also proposed that Israel 
send a team of researchers to Japan. Mr. Harisshu is visiting 
Japan at the invitation of Minister Mori. 

