<ABS>  Japan </ABS>
<DATE1>   31 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> Nuclear Engineering </F>
<H3> <TI>   PNC Starts Core Flow Distribution Evaluation Tests for Monju </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94FE0170D Tokyo KAGAKU KOGYO NIPPO in Japanese 5 Nov 93 p 12 
--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94FE0170D </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KAGAKU KOGYO NIPPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] The Power Reactor and Nuclear Fuel Development 
Corporation (PNC) has completed the loading of internal core 
fuel assemblies (108 units) in the prototype fast breeder 
reactor (FBR) ``Monju'' (rated output 280,000 kilowatts), which 
started on 13 October, and it began evaluation tests on flow 
distribution in the core on 4 November. In these tests, 
instruments to measure flow will be installed in the reactor and 
the flow of natrium circulating among the fuel assemblies will 
be measured and evaluated. 
  To cool the ``Monju's'' core efficiently, the coolant 
natrium 
is circulated in response to the amount of heat generated by 
core fuel assemblies and blanket fuel assemblies, important 
components of the core. Evaluation testing will continue until 
around the beginning of February 1994. 

</TEXT>

